34:42.583 --> 34:45.291
-You're an inspiration. It's incredible.
-To so many.

34:45.375 --> 34:47.250
You're really owning that pain.

34:47.333 --> 34:51.041
You know, Jack, I feel like
there's some kind of conversation

34:51.125 --> 34:54.500
that we need to be having here.
Is there any message

34:54.583 --> 34:58.750
that you would like
to send to your, uh, ex, DJ Chello?

34:59.791 --> 35:01.083
You know, um…

35:01.166 --> 35:02.625
[Jack] If there's something--

35:02.708 --> 35:04.291
-Yeah.
-Right here in this camera.

35:04.375 --> 35:07.666
Tell him. As if that was him.
You tell him exactly what you're thinking.

35:07.750 --> 35:09.208
Okay, um… [clears throat]

35:10.541 --> 35:11.500
[sighs]

35:11.583 --> 35:12.666
Chell.

35:13.500 --> 35:19.250
[sighs] I still love you,
and, um, after many sleepless nights,

35:20.750 --> 35:21.833
three,

35:22.541 --> 35:23.875
I wanna take you back.

35:23.958 --> 35:25.708
I'm sorry. Whoa, uh…

35:25.791 --> 35:26.875
-Is that okay?
-Yeah.

35:26.958 --> 35:29.875
-[Brie on TV] He cheated on you.
-Oh, my God. You guys…

35:29.958 --> 35:31.666
Yeah. I do.

35:31.750 --> 35:34.000
-Diddly just exploded.
-So did Vroom Vroom.

35:34.083 --> 35:36.250
BASH News just sent me
eight push notifications.

35:36.333 --> 35:38.166
-About this?
-Yeah, look.

35:38.250 --> 35:40.708
My phone just purchased
DJ Chello's latest single.

35:40.791 --> 35:42.875
What the… It just did that without asking.

35:42.958 --> 35:45.791
I'm being told that
we have DJ Chello live on a Mugg link.

35:45.875 --> 35:48.791
-What's he got to say for himself?
-I love the producers here.

35:48.875 --> 35:50.125
Hey, baby doll. Hey.

35:50.208 --> 35:52.083
-Hi. Hi, baby. [crying]
-[Jack] He's in tears.

35:52.166 --> 35:54.083
-Your kid messed up bad.
-I know.

35:54.166 --> 35:56.666
Lady Baroque wasn't wearing
any panties in the club that night.

35:56.750 --> 35:58.416
-It's fine.
-I just got all crazy.

35:58.500 --> 36:00.416
I wasn't thinking straight.
I made a mistake.

36:00.500 --> 36:02.375
But, look, it's always been you.

36:02.458 --> 36:04.791
Oh! I get it. It's okay.

36:04.875 --> 36:07.583
I hooked up with her too,
last year at the Music Globes

36:07.666 --> 36:10.000
right before I ran off
with that power forward from the Nuggets,

36:10.083 --> 36:12.250
and none of that matters.

36:12.333 --> 36:15.916
What about "Forget breakup sex.
Try breakup relationship"?

36:16.000 --> 36:17.166
-That's good.
-Come on.

36:17.250 --> 36:20.166
"Ten famous second chances
for two-timers," guys.

36:20.250 --> 36:21.166
It's on a plate.

36:21.250 --> 36:25.125
I've been scared, but, honestly,
I'm not scared anymore.

36:25.208 --> 36:26.041
Okay.

36:26.125 --> 36:28.958
My little bumblebee, will you marry me?

36:29.041 --> 36:31.625
-[gasps] Oh, my God. Of course.
-[Jack] Oh, wow.

36:31.708 --> 36:33.208
-Chell, of course.
-[DJ Chello] Yes!

36:33.291 --> 36:35.416
-Yes!
-That's sick.

36:35.500 --> 36:36.333
[DJ Chello] Yes!

36:36.416 --> 36:38.791
All right, DJ Chello.

36:38.875 --> 36:40.875
-[cell phones vibrating]
-What is happening?

36:40.958 --> 36:41.916
Just bought another.

36:42.000 --> 36:44.916
-Who are these people again?
-They're like the biggest names…

36:45.000 --> 36:46.500
[Brie chuckles]

36:46.583 --> 36:49.625
Well, the fireworks
have certainly gone off today.

36:49.708 --> 36:50.875
-They have.
-What a zinger!

36:50.958 --> 36:52.458
[Jack] Yes, they have.

36:52.541 --> 36:55.250
From a wedding proposal
to a little science experiment.

36:55.333 --> 36:57.250
I'll need a temple rub
and a martini later on.

36:57.333 --> 37:02.041
[Brie] Our last guests today have made
a pretty big discovery in space.

37:02.125 --> 37:04.041
Astronomer Dr. Randall Mindy

37:04.125 --> 37:07.208
and PhD candidate
Miss Kate Dibiasky are here.

37:07.291 --> 37:08.333
Welcome to the show.

37:08.416 --> 37:11.583
Can I ask you one thing before we go
any further? I have to know this.

37:11.666 --> 37:14.208
Is there life out there?

37:14.291 --> 37:17.708
-Can you tell us? Yes or no, final answer.
-We don't have the data.

37:17.791 --> 37:19.958
But sure, in the vastness
of space, why not?

37:20.041 --> 37:21.541
Yes, aliens are real.

37:21.625 --> 37:24.166
I knew I'd like this guy.
Didn't I tell? You owe me 50 bucks.

37:24.250 --> 37:27.000
[Mindy] I'm not saying there's
little green men in flying saucers--

37:27.083 --> 37:30.208
-Please don't encourage him, Dr. Mindy.
-That's what he's saying.

37:30.291 --> 37:31.708
We'll never get out of here.

37:31.791 --> 37:33.541
Now, Jack was having some fun here.

37:33.625 --> 37:35.166
-Dad looks great.
-What did…

37:35.250 --> 37:37.583
-Doesn't he look good?
-They did something with his beard.

37:37.666 --> 37:39.583
[Brie] With the aliens…

37:39.666 --> 37:41.458
[chuckling] Really… He really does.

37:41.541 --> 37:43.625
-[Jack] So much.
-[Brie chuckles] Dr. Randall…

37:43.708 --> 37:47.125
You'll regret it. Now, look,
Jack's just having some fun here

37:47.208 --> 37:48.875
with the aliens or whatever,

37:48.958 --> 37:53.250
but there's a New York Herald story
that's just come out that talks about…

37:53.333 --> 37:55.375
Keep it right there. You're doing good.

37:55.458 --> 37:57.833
-…the two of you have made.
-[Mindy] That's right, Brie.

37:57.916 --> 38:00.958
Kate was, um, observing supernovas…

38:01.041 --> 38:02.583
Yo, that's your girl?

38:02.666 --> 38:05.083
-Yeah.
-Not bad.

38:05.166 --> 38:09.625
…an absolutely shocking
and once-in-a-lifetime discovery.

38:09.708 --> 38:13.000
I had no idea that Subaru made telescopes.

38:13.083 --> 38:16.166
This has to be exciting.
Tell us what you found, Miss Diabasky.

38:16.250 --> 38:20.250
Um, I was monitoring exploding stars

38:20.333 --> 38:26.750
to help measure
the expansion of the universe and--

38:26.833 --> 38:28.875
-For your PhD, right?
-Yeah.

38:28.958 --> 38:33.125
[Kate] I saw something I didn't recognize.

38:34.541 --> 38:36.041
It was a comet.

38:36.125 --> 38:36.958
[sighs]

38:37.041 --> 38:38.166
[Kate] A big one.

38:40.708 --> 38:44.583
It's headed directly at Earth,
and it really likely will hit.

38:45.916 --> 38:47.791
This sounds very, very exciting.

38:47.875 --> 38:50.458
Exploding stars, like,
stars actually explode.

38:50.541 --> 38:51.708
Um, how big is this thing?

38:51.791 --> 38:54.083
Can it destroy someone's house?
Is that possible?

38:54.166 --> 38:57.333
Well, Comet Dibiasky, which is
what it will officially be named--

38:57.416 --> 38:58.833
-[Jack] After her?
-Yeah, after her.

38:58.916 --> 39:01.583
-[Brie] Congratulations.
-[Jack] What an honor. Congratulations.

39:01.666 --> 39:04.166
It's somewhere between
six and nine kilometers across.

39:04.250 --> 39:05.583
-So--
-It's big.

39:05.666 --> 39:08.875
It would damage the entire planet.

39:08.958 --> 39:10.583
Not just a house, you know?

39:10.666 --> 39:11.708
The entire planet.

39:11.791 --> 39:14.708
Okay, as it's damaging,
will it hit this one house in particular

39:14.791 --> 39:17.875
that's right on the coast of New Jersey?
It's my ex-wife's house.

39:17.958 --> 39:19.208
Can we make that happen?

39:19.291 --> 39:21.708
You and Shelly have
a great relationship. Stop.

39:21.791 --> 39:23.125
You need to stop.

39:23.208 --> 39:26.125
I will, but in all fairness,
I actually paid for the house.

39:26.208 --> 39:27.500
[Brie] I'm so sorry.

39:27.583 --> 39:30.583
I'm sorry, are we not being clear?

39:31.916 --> 39:33.791
We're trying to tell you

39:33.875 --> 39:37.291
that the entire planet
is about to be destroyed.

39:37.958 --> 39:40.291
-[Jack] Okay, um…
-[Brie] Well, it's, you know…

39:40.375 --> 39:43.625
It's something we do around here.
We just keep the bad news light.

39:43.708 --> 39:45.625
Right. It helps the medicine go down.

39:45.708 --> 39:47.666
Speaking of medicine, tomorrow we've got--

39:47.750 --> 39:51.541
Well, maybe the destruction
of the entire planet

39:52.458 --> 39:53.833
isn't supposed to be fun.

39:54.625 --> 39:58.250
Maybe it's supposed to be terrifying.

39:58.333 --> 39:59.333
And unsettling.

39:59.416 --> 40:01.125
[Adul] No, please don't do that.

40:01.208 --> 40:03.333
-And you should stay up all night…
-[Adul] Please.

40:03.416 --> 40:05.250
…every night crying,

40:05.333 --> 40:09.750
when we're all 100%
for sure gonna fucking die!

40:10.500 --> 40:12.416
-[crying]
-Hey, Kate.

40:12.500 --> 40:13.500
[Kate] I'm sorry.

40:14.875 --> 40:15.708
Hey, man.

40:16.375 --> 40:19.708
My brother has bipolar disorder.
So if you ever need anyone to talk…

40:20.708 --> 40:22.583
-Uh… [inhales sharply]
-Okay.

40:22.666 --> 40:25.583
Is she always like that?

40:26.291 --> 40:28.083
-I--
-[Brie] Something I said?

40:28.166 --> 40:30.083
-[Jack and Brie chuckle]
-[Jack] Right?

40:30.166 --> 40:33.625
Maybe I should have given her
that extra Xanax that I had.

40:33.708 --> 40:34.708
[Jack and Brie chuckle]

40:34.791 --> 40:38.208
Listen, if you don't have enough,
we all have enough around here for her.

40:38.291 --> 40:41.166
A spoonful of Xanax
makes the medicine go down, right?

40:41.250 --> 40:42.916
[Jack] That's right. That's good.

40:43.916 --> 40:47.166
-We're gonna have to get you back.
-[Jack] I knew I'd like this guy.

40:47.250 --> 40:49.333
-Is he a plant? [laughing]
-[Jack] I knew it.

40:49.416 --> 40:50.333
[Brie] Okay.

40:50.416 --> 40:52.791
Well, the handsome astronomer

40:52.875 --> 40:56.375
can come back anytime,
but the yelling lady, not so much.

40:56.458 --> 40:59.416
[Jack] Not so much. Join us tomorrow
when our guest will be the man

40:59.500 --> 41:03.083
that many say will challenge
President Orlean in two years.

41:03.166 --> 41:05.166
Senator Jeff Lerner will be here.

41:05.250 --> 41:08.000
And wrongly-convicted murderer,
Michelle Weems,

41:08.083 --> 41:12.375
talks to us about her controversial
third-place finish on Celebrity Dance Off.

41:12.458 --> 41:15.833
-I thought she would've won.
-Yes. I still think she's guilty.

41:15.916 --> 41:18.083
-That's The Daily Rip, guys.
-[Brie] Have a great day.

41:18.666 --> 41:20.583
-[producer] And we're out!
-The show's over?

41:20.666 --> 41:21.958
-I mean, didn't…
-[Jack] Yeah.

41:22.041 --> 41:24.500
-Did what we wanted to say come across?
-No, it's over.

41:24.583 --> 41:28.500
You were great, but I think mullet girl,
she probably needs some media training.

41:29.625 --> 41:31.291
-Really?
-Yeah, no, terrible, buddy.

41:31.375 --> 41:33.916
[Brie] Oh… Thanks. Thanks, Billy.

41:34.000 --> 41:39.500
Uh, we usually get drinks at Aundrine's
after our five o'clock staff meeting.

41:39.583 --> 41:42.041
You know, it's fun. You should come.

41:42.125 --> 41:45.041
Oh, I'll have to see.
Thank you for the invitation. Thank you.

41:45.583 --> 41:46.583
Mmm-hmm.

41:47.916 --> 41:49.291
Kate? Kate?

41:49.375 --> 41:52.250
-Hey. You were awesome.
-Oh, thanks.

41:52.333 --> 41:54.291
Can I get a photo of you for my portfolio?

41:54.375 --> 41:55.666
-Yeah, sure.
-Thanks.

41:55.750 --> 41:57.083
-[camera clicks]
-Thank you.

41:57.666 --> 41:59.166
[woman] You can see this spike here

41:59.250 --> 42:01.375
is when Riley Bina
asked to take DJ Chello back

42:01.458 --> 42:02.750
on the segment before you.

42:02.833 --> 42:06.041
We saw engagement across
all social media platforms.

42:06.125 --> 42:08.916
Hmm. And what about our story?

42:09.000 --> 42:11.958
[woman] Randall and Kate,

42:12.041 --> 42:15.750
your TV appearance got some nice traffic
when Miss Dibiasky cursed.

42:15.833 --> 42:19.041
But, unfortunately,
there was an immediate backlash

42:19.125 --> 42:20.833
-that quickly became a meme.
-[Kate gasps]

42:20.916 --> 42:22.208
Oh, Jesus.

42:22.875 --> 42:26.250
-Oh, that's terrible.
-They just think I'm crazy.

42:26.333 --> 42:29.333
I mean, look at that.
That's so unnecessary.

42:30.708 --> 42:33.125
-You can move on, Erin.
-Yeah.

42:33.208 --> 42:35.916
That is just so…
Is that even allowed on the Internet or…

42:36.000 --> 42:37.625
I think that's Photoshop, Kate.

42:37.708 --> 42:40.083
[Erin] The trick is
to not take it personal…

42:40.166 --> 42:44.458
[chuckling] Dr. Mindy, on the other hand,
had some very high favorables.

42:44.541 --> 42:49.125
Vegan*Babe wrote,
"Meow! Me likey hunky Star Man."

42:49.208 --> 42:52.208
Uh, some accounts called him
"The Bedroom Eyes Doomsday Prophet"

42:52.291 --> 42:55.083
or A-I-L-F, which means
"astronomer I'd like to fuck."

42:55.166 --> 42:56.041
[people] Oh…

42:56.125 --> 42:58.666
I don't see what that has
to do with anything, do you?

42:59.375 --> 43:02.500
And that's everything.

43:02.583 --> 43:05.666
We did not feature or push on any sites,

43:05.750 --> 43:09.083
and clicks overall were below
basic weather and traffic stories.

43:09.166 --> 43:10.416
[scoffs]

43:10.500 --> 43:12.500
So that… That… That's it?

43:12.583 --> 43:14.333
-[Kate] I knew it.
-That's it.

43:15.250 --> 43:17.833
-Thank you, Erin.
-[Erin] Yeah, no problem.

43:18.500 --> 43:20.750
[Mindy] I don't… I don't understand.

43:20.833 --> 43:22.666
I don't understand. There's no response.

43:22.750 --> 43:27.375
There's absolutely no…
Why aren't people terrified?

43:27.458 --> 43:29.458
What do we have to say?
What do we have to do?

43:29.541 --> 43:32.916
There are scientists in Mexico and Spain
who are currently going through the data,

43:33.000 --> 43:34.708
and, uh, South Korea has expressed--

43:34.791 --> 43:36.500
-That's great. South Korea.
-Hey.

43:36.583 --> 43:39.041
Let us not bullshit each other.

43:39.125 --> 43:42.791
The bottom line is,
you guys told us the science was 100%.

43:42.875 --> 43:44.625
It's not. Now we look like idiots.

43:44.708 --> 43:47.291
-No. Who said the science is not 100%?
-Excuse me?

43:47.375 --> 43:50.250
I wanna talk to this person.
You tell me who said the science--

43:50.333 --> 43:53.333
Dr. Jocelyn Calder, the head of NASA,

43:53.416 --> 43:56.625
just came out calling it
"more near-miss hysteria."

43:56.708 --> 43:58.625
She's the one
who told us not to say anything.

43:58.708 --> 44:00.083
"More near-miss hysteria."

44:00.166 --> 44:01.291
Is she even an astronomer?

44:01.375 --> 44:04.458
She's the head of NASA, but maybe
she doesn't know what she's talking about.

44:04.541 --> 44:05.958
She's the head of NASA, but look,

44:06.041 --> 44:09.875
she's a "former anesthesiologist
and a President Orlean super donor."

44:09.958 --> 44:11.583
Let's not be dramatic here.

44:11.666 --> 44:12.666
It's all corrupt.

44:12.750 --> 44:16.416
Yes, but the point is that Adul's right.
There's still serious debate.

44:16.500 --> 44:18.708
And now the Herald has egg on its face.

44:18.791 --> 44:20.916
We've taken that story as far as it goes.

44:21.666 --> 44:25.625
Ladies, gentlemen,
I wish you a very pleasant end of times.

44:25.708 --> 44:27.708
[Mindy] It's not a goddamn story, okay?

44:30.208 --> 44:32.916
We have precisely six months, ten days,

44:33.000 --> 44:36.250
two hours, 11 minutes and 41 seconds,

44:36.333 --> 44:39.000
until a comet twice the size of Chicxulub

44:39.083 --> 44:41.833
tears through our atmosphere
and extincts all life on Earth.

44:41.916 --> 44:44.833
[chuckles] When did you
do those calculations?

44:45.666 --> 44:48.250
I put the moment of impact on a diet app.

44:48.333 --> 44:51.958
So, impact is when my diet ends.

44:52.041 --> 44:56.125
Only I'm not on a diet.
I'm just crying five times a day.

44:56.208 --> 44:58.125
-I'm scared.
-Hey, come on. Come on.

44:58.833 --> 45:01.416
Everyone should be
panicking right now, okay?

45:01.500 --> 45:03.416
-Don't cry. Come on.
-[Kate] I know.

45:03.500 --> 45:04.750
[cell phone chimes]

45:04.833 --> 45:05.833
[sighs]

45:06.833 --> 45:08.291
That prick!

45:08.375 --> 45:09.791
[upbeat tense music playing]

45:16.500 --> 45:17.666
[Mindy] What happened?

45:17.750 --> 45:20.083
Guess my boyfriend just broke up with me.

45:20.166 --> 45:24.500
-God, what a day. What a day…
-[crying]

45:32.666 --> 45:35.958
You're gonna die!
You're gonna die! You're…

45:36.041 --> 45:38.125
[slow rumbling]

45:46.291 --> 45:49.708
[reporter on TV] It started with
a photo many thought was an armpit

45:49.791 --> 45:52.458
or the chin of a man with a strange beard.

45:52.541 --> 45:54.833
But what's emerging now is a scandal…

45:54.916 --> 45:57.833
President Orlean sent
her Supreme Court nominee

45:57.916 --> 46:00.583
a cell phone picture of her private parts.

46:00.666 --> 46:02.708
-Holy crap!
-[woman] It's clickbait material.

46:02.791 --> 46:05.250
Is this what you want
in your country as a leader?

46:05.333 --> 46:07.708
Isn't she the same person
who told poor people

46:07.791 --> 46:11.833
that if they don't wanna be poor,
they should pick better lottery numbers?

46:11.916 --> 46:12.958
She actually said that.

46:13.041 --> 46:14.541
A source also confirmed to me that

46:14.625 --> 46:16.750
the two have been
having an affair for years.

46:16.833 --> 46:18.416
And as recently as yesterday…

46:18.500 --> 46:22.583
Members of my party
are currently drawing up a formal censure

46:22.666 --> 46:23.625
of the president,

46:24.583 --> 46:25.500
Janie Orlean…

46:25.583 --> 46:26.916
[Mindy] Oh, my God, honey.

46:27.000 --> 46:29.791
This guy doesn't even know
what a heliocentric orbit is,

46:29.875 --> 46:32.625
and he's calling me a crackpot. [chuckles]

46:32.708 --> 46:33.708
