Hi. Oh, Brie, you look fabulous.

1:03:04.791 --> 1:03:05.791
As always.

1:03:06.958 --> 1:03:08.333
Is he allowed to be in here?

1:03:08.416 --> 1:03:12.291
Yeah, he's a Platinum Eagle level donor
to the campaign. He has full clearance.

1:03:12.375 --> 1:03:14.000
[man on radio] Launch mission array.

1:03:14.083 --> 1:03:17.625
[sighs] Molly kicking in right now.
Timed that shit perfect.

1:03:17.708 --> 1:03:20.666
Ten, nine, eight…

1:03:20.750 --> 1:03:24.791
-seven, six, five, four…
-[all cheering]

1:03:24.875 --> 1:03:26.125
Three…

1:03:26.208 --> 1:03:27.583
-[barking]
-Ah…

1:03:32.416 --> 1:03:34.791
[indistinct chatter]

1:03:34.875 --> 1:03:37.875
[soaring choral music playing]

1:03:40.541 --> 1:03:41.750
Thank God!

1:04:00.083 --> 1:04:03.541
[Drask] ♪ Oh, Susannah
Don't you cry for me ♪

1:04:03.625 --> 1:04:07.958
♪ I come from Alabama
With a banjo on my knee, hey! ♪

1:04:08.041 --> 1:04:09.541
[camera shutters clicking]

1:04:09.625 --> 1:04:11.583
[Oglethorpe] We didn't lose
any satellites.

1:04:11.666 --> 1:04:14.916
Margin of error
was for two to malfunction.

1:04:15.000 --> 1:04:19.166
Hey, Madam President, may I have a word
with you outside for a moment, please?

1:04:19.791 --> 1:04:20.916
Oh, my God.

1:04:21.000 --> 1:04:23.791
Mission success probability
is already increased to 81%.

1:04:23.875 --> 1:04:25.875
[man] Outstanding.

1:04:26.583 --> 1:04:27.750
-[Peter] Janie, now!
-[gasps]

1:04:27.833 --> 1:04:30.583
I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry.

1:04:30.666 --> 1:04:32.250
Peter, I didn't mean…

1:04:36.500 --> 1:04:41.708
[Drask] And a big hello to that beautiful
blue ball down there we all call home.

1:04:42.208 --> 1:04:45.625
All those proud white folks working hard.

1:04:46.125 --> 1:04:47.083
God bless you.

1:04:47.875 --> 1:04:50.125
Just a different generation. Yeah.

1:04:50.791 --> 1:04:53.666
I also wanna say hello
to all the Indians out there.

1:04:53.750 --> 1:04:54.833
Both kinds.

1:04:54.916 --> 1:04:59.041
You know, the ones with the elephants
and the ones with the bow and arrows.

1:04:59.708 --> 1:05:01.500
Hey, why haven't you guys ever teamed up?

1:05:01.583 --> 1:05:03.458
[chuckles] How cool would that be, huh?

1:05:03.541 --> 1:05:05.458
I wanna say hello
to all the gays out there.

1:05:05.541 --> 1:05:07.875
-Commander, booster ejection is imminent.
-Huh?

1:05:07.958 --> 1:05:10.208
-Let's keep comm on mission.
-Oh. Roger that.

1:05:10.708 --> 1:05:12.625
[soaring music continues]

1:05:20.750 --> 1:05:22.666
[man on radio] Separation confirmed.

1:05:22.750 --> 1:05:24.500
-Separation confirmed.
-Whoo!

1:05:25.166 --> 1:05:27.541
[speaking French]

1:05:29.083 --> 1:05:30.166
Was that French?

1:05:31.458 --> 1:05:37.000
Yes, it is. It means, "the angels soar
to the heavens." It's, um…

1:05:38.333 --> 1:05:42.458
It's from a 14th-century poem
I studied in Dartmouth.

1:05:42.541 --> 1:05:45.875
And just watching this,
it just made me think of it,

1:05:47.000 --> 1:05:48.416
and think of you.

1:05:49.500 --> 1:05:50.500
God, I can't…

1:05:51.375 --> 1:05:52.333
Can't…

1:05:53.083 --> 1:05:55.958
[upbeat tense music playing]

1:06:01.583 --> 1:06:04.125
[men chanting] Go! Go! Go!

1:06:04.208 --> 1:06:05.708
-[groans]
-[laughter]

1:06:05.791 --> 1:06:08.666
I think I probably should go
to the [bleep] hospital and see what they…

1:06:08.750 --> 1:06:10.708
[people on video] Launch challenge!

1:06:10.791 --> 1:06:13.666
[people chanting on video] Go! Go! Go!

1:06:17.458 --> 1:06:19.583
Everyone, I have just received

1:06:19.666 --> 1:06:23.416
some critical information
concerning our mission.

1:06:23.500 --> 1:06:25.208
[people clamoring]

1:06:32.625 --> 1:06:34.291
Looks like it's turning around.

1:06:37.125 --> 1:06:40.250
No, it's not. It's a course correction.

1:06:40.333 --> 1:06:41.875
It's pretty standard.

1:06:41.958 --> 1:06:43.416
I was in the Navy.

1:06:45.083 --> 1:06:47.375
Nope. It's turning around.

1:06:47.458 --> 1:06:51.166
[reporter] Seems to be
some confusion here amongst the crowd,

1:06:51.250 --> 1:06:52.875
but I'm not gonna lie to you.

1:06:52.958 --> 1:06:55.916
This reporter
is at a loss for words right now.

1:06:56.000 --> 1:06:59.208
It's definitely turning around.

1:06:59.291 --> 1:07:01.416
I'm looking straight at it.

1:07:01.500 --> 1:07:05.500
Drask's ship is definitely turning around.

1:07:07.916 --> 1:07:10.291
Does anyone know
what the fuck just happened?

1:07:16.208 --> 1:07:17.583
It's still locked.

1:07:17.666 --> 1:07:20.375
I just don't… I don't understand
what could've happened.

1:07:20.458 --> 1:07:23.250
I mean, the mission was working, right?
Everything was on track.

1:07:23.333 --> 1:07:26.166
Yeah. I mean,
it could've been anything, uh…

1:07:26.250 --> 1:07:31.958
Guidance system could've malfunctioned,
uh, nuke destabilized, myriad of things.

1:07:32.583 --> 1:07:35.625
Who was that guy that walked into
the Situation Room? He looked familiar.

1:07:35.708 --> 1:07:42.083
That was Peter Isherwell, CEO of BASH,
and the third richest human ever.

1:07:42.166 --> 1:07:46.125
He's the guy that, uh, bought
the Gutenberg Bible and lost it.

1:07:46.208 --> 1:07:47.333
[door opens]

1:07:47.416 --> 1:07:48.916
[Jason] Sorry to keep you waiting.

1:07:49.000 --> 1:07:51.833
Things are, uh, extremely fluid.

1:07:53.291 --> 1:07:56.916
Dr. Randall, you are now the Chief
Science Advisor to the White House.

1:07:57.000 --> 1:07:57.833
What?

1:07:57.916 --> 1:08:00.666
As such, you need to attend
an emergency Cabinet meeting

1:08:00.750 --> 1:08:02.000
where you will be debriefed.

1:08:02.083 --> 1:08:03.083
What about us?

1:08:03.666 --> 1:08:06.166
You do not have clearance
for this, sweetheart. Don't trip.

1:08:06.250 --> 1:08:09.000
Got you some crackers, some waters.

1:08:09.083 --> 1:08:10.750
You don't need to throw it on the floor.

1:08:10.833 --> 1:08:12.375
Gonna be three, four hours, tops.

1:08:12.458 --> 1:08:15.583
Here, Kate. I don't know
why he threw 'em down. Here.

1:08:15.666 --> 1:08:17.750
What if we have to go to the bathroom?

1:08:17.833 --> 1:08:21.250
We'll lay out some newspaper for you.
Grab you a can of Febreze.

1:08:21.333 --> 1:08:23.208
[Oglethorpe] Short, sweet
and simple science.

1:08:23.291 --> 1:08:24.958
I'll be back. All right. Come on.

1:08:25.041 --> 1:08:27.083
[Oglethorpe]
Science tells the truth, Randall.

1:08:27.833 --> 1:08:28.791
[sighs]

1:08:28.875 --> 1:08:30.500
Fuck. Do you wanna come?

1:08:30.583 --> 1:08:31.500
Yeah.

1:08:33.625 --> 1:08:35.625
[Orlean] Ladies and gentlemen,
what we thought,

1:08:35.708 --> 1:08:40.708
what the world thought
was an impending and terrifying danger,

1:08:41.916 --> 1:08:44.625
turns out to be
an astonishing opportunity.

1:08:44.708 --> 1:08:47.166
Our allies are very confused
and demanding answers--

1:08:47.250 --> 1:08:48.541
Well, tell 'em to wait.

1:08:49.583 --> 1:08:54.666
According to the most recent
spectrometer readings of Comet Dibiasky,

1:08:54.750 --> 1:08:57.833
made by the astrogeologists
at BASH Cellular,

1:08:59.583 --> 1:09:01.291
we've discovered something.

1:09:02.250 --> 1:09:05.000
Something truly miraculous.

1:09:06.458 --> 1:09:08.125
Peter. Peter?

1:09:08.208 --> 1:09:10.000
-Oh, thank you, Janie.
-[chuckles]

1:09:12.208 --> 1:09:14.708
As, uh… As some of you may know,

1:09:14.791 --> 1:09:17.541
the most valuable minerals in the world

1:09:17.625 --> 1:09:19.750
are fast becoming those that are deployed

1:09:19.833 --> 1:09:24.000
in the manufacture
of cell phones and, uh, computers.

1:09:24.083 --> 1:09:27.583
Yttrium, terbium, osmium, dysprosium,
on and on and on.

1:09:27.666 --> 1:09:29.000
We're running short.

1:09:29.083 --> 1:09:31.916
Uh, and the problem
is exacerbated, of course,

1:09:32.000 --> 1:09:37.916
because China has her big panda paw
firmly on almost all the mines

1:09:38.000 --> 1:09:41.500
that produce
these valuable rare Earth assets.

1:09:41.583 --> 1:09:43.625
So you can imagine. [laughing]

1:09:43.708 --> 1:09:44.666
Wow!

1:09:44.750 --> 1:09:48.541
Just how happy we were at BASH

1:09:48.625 --> 1:09:52.250
when our astrogeologists discovered

1:09:52.333 --> 1:09:57.000
and then determined that this comet,
hurtling towards us from deep space,

1:09:57.083 --> 1:10:02.833
actually contains at least $32 trillion
of these critical materials.

1:10:02.916 --> 1:10:04.666
Critical to technology.

1:10:04.750 --> 1:10:05.958
If we're to proceed--

1:10:06.041 --> 1:10:08.541
I'm sorry. Is that why
you aborted this entire mission,

1:10:08.625 --> 1:10:11.541
is because you're trying to mine
the comet for rare minerals?

1:10:11.625 --> 1:10:13.708
[Orlean] I think
we should hold all questions

1:10:13.791 --> 1:10:16.458
until the end of the presentation,

1:10:16.541 --> 1:10:20.125
and you might find
that your questions are answered.

1:10:20.666 --> 1:10:21.750
Yes, Madam President.

1:10:21.833 --> 1:10:24.875
When you…
When the other metals are factored in,

1:10:24.958 --> 1:10:27.333
the comet actually contains

1:10:27.416 --> 1:10:31.541
almost $140 trillion worth of assets.

1:10:31.625 --> 1:10:32.916
[Jason] Buck-forty trilli.

1:10:33.416 --> 1:10:35.291
-[Orlean] Yeah…
-[laughter]

1:10:35.375 --> 1:10:40.000
What do these trillions of dollars
even matter if we're all gonna die--

1:10:40.083 --> 1:10:42.458
[woman] I was about to ask
the same question, Janie.

1:10:42.541 --> 1:10:43.666
Why weren't we consulted?

1:10:43.750 --> 1:10:45.250
All due respect, Madam President…

1:10:45.333 --> 1:10:47.833
Oh, no! What if we're rich and we're safe?

1:10:49.000 --> 1:10:53.125
[Kate] I've gone over it
again and again and again in my head

1:10:54.875 --> 1:10:56.791
and I still can't make sense of it.

1:10:58.750 --> 1:11:03.791
He's a three-star general.
He works at the Pentagon.

1:11:05.916 --> 1:11:09.000
Why would he charge us for free snacks?

1:11:09.083 --> 1:11:12.750
One time, I met Sting,

1:11:13.708 --> 1:11:18.291
and I swear to God,
he farted right in front of me.

1:11:19.333 --> 1:11:24.458
Didn't break eye contact
and didn't even say "excuse me."

1:11:27.500 --> 1:11:31.083
And the thing is,
he actually pulled it off. [chuckles]

1:11:32.375 --> 1:11:34.875
'Cause I still found him
to be quite charming.

1:11:35.916 --> 1:11:40.333
[whispering] Guys, we have to talk.
Come on, let's go. Come on, now.

1:11:41.416 --> 1:11:44.625
It's insane. Like, completely insane.

1:11:44.708 --> 1:11:46.041
[Kate] It will never work.

1:11:46.125 --> 1:11:48.291
I had the exact same reaction.

1:11:48.375 --> 1:11:51.500
This is a nine-kilometer-wide
planet-killer we're talking about,

1:11:51.583 --> 1:11:53.041
not roaming charges.

1:11:53.125 --> 1:11:59.041
Look, I… I was confused and outraged
that they turned this mission around too,

1:11:59.125 --> 1:12:01.708
but they've got
Gary Talcamont from Stanford

1:12:01.791 --> 1:12:03.958
and Lisa Inez from Princeton
on their team.

1:12:04.041 --> 1:12:07.750
I mean, this is next-generation
cutting-edge technology.

1:12:07.833 --> 1:12:14.625
Obviously, one giant comet is a major
and existential, uh, threat to our planet,

1:12:14.708 --> 1:12:20.000
but 30 smaller meteoroids, we can handle.

1:12:20.916 --> 1:12:26.625
Our BEADS, that stands for
BASH, uh, Explore and Acquire Drones,

1:12:26.708 --> 1:12:28.083
that you see here,

1:12:28.166 --> 1:12:30.833
attach themselves to the comet

1:12:30.916 --> 1:12:33.375
and scan it with nanotechnology

1:12:33.458 --> 1:12:36.583
developed by
Nobel Prize-winning scientist,

1:12:36.666 --> 1:12:37.666
Dr. Gary Talcamont.

1:12:37.750 --> 1:12:40.500
And then we immediately deploy, don't we?

1:12:40.583 --> 1:12:42.833
Nobel and Polonsky prize-winning scientist

1:12:42.916 --> 1:12:48.250
Dr. Inez's micro-targeted,
quantum fission, uh, explosives.

1:12:48.333 --> 1:12:51.625
You see, deep into the object…

1:12:51.708 --> 1:12:54.458
Dr. Inez, would you like
to explain what's happening?

1:12:54.541 --> 1:12:55.416
Thank you, Peter.

1:12:55.500 --> 1:12:58.250
We've been developing
phase-fission reactions

1:12:58.333 --> 1:13:00.375
in the CERN particle accelerator

1:13:00.458 --> 1:13:03.125
that can splinter the comet
into smaller pieces

1:13:03.208 --> 1:13:05.333
with breathtaking accuracy.

1:13:05.416 --> 1:13:08.791
These segments are then steered
and decelerated by each BEAD

1:13:08.875 --> 1:13:13.625
into the Pacific Ocean for reclamation
by waiting US Navy ships.

1:13:13.708 --> 1:13:15.666
And when these… Thank you.

1:13:15.750 --> 1:13:19.875
And when these treasures
from heaven are claimed,

1:13:19.958 --> 1:13:23.916
poverty as we know it,
social injustice, loss of biodiversity,

1:13:24.000 --> 1:13:26.708
all these multitudes of problems

1:13:26.791 --> 1:13:30.125
are just gonna become relics of the past

1:13:30.208 --> 1:13:35.625
and humanity is gonna stride through
the Pillars of Boaz and Jachin naked

1:13:35.708 --> 1:13:38.250
into the the glory of a golden age…

1:13:38.333 --> 1:13:41.500
And is this nanotech work peer-reviewed?

1:13:41.583 --> 1:13:45.166
Well, I haven't reviewed the data,
but it's been modeled.

1:13:45.250 --> 1:13:47.125
Has any of this been peer-reviewed?

1:13:48.000 --> 1:13:48.833
Nope.

1:13:48.916 --> 1:13:51.250
Interplanetary, interstellar,

1:13:51.333 --> 1:13:56.125
intergalactic existence
for the human race.

1:13:56.208 --> 1:13:57.583
[applause]

1:13:59.125 --> 1:14:00.916
[Orlean] Your mouth to God's ear.

1:14:01.458 --> 1:14:05.041
I understand the wealth
that they can extract from this comet,

1:14:05.125 --> 1:14:06.291
it can end world hunger.

1:14:06.375 --> 1:14:08.166
-[Oglethorpe] Oh, I see.
-[Kate laughing]

1:14:08.250 --> 1:14:10.833
-Why are you laughing?
-[Oglethorpe] That's true. No, I see.

1:14:10.916 --> 1:14:15.333
So that's the pretty little bow they're
putting around this line of bullshit.

1:14:15.416 --> 1:14:17.250
I bet they'll say freedom and puppies too.

1:14:17.333 --> 1:14:18.166
-All right.
-Yeah.

1:14:18.250 --> 1:14:21.916
You want me to quit the mission?
I'll quit the mission. That's fine.

1:14:22.416 --> 1:14:25.708
But you have to understand,
this is now beyond our control.

1:14:25.791 --> 1:14:27.208
They have all the power.

1:14:27.291 --> 1:14:29.958
So who do you want
in the actual room to make sure

1:14:30.041 --> 1:14:33.000
this whole thing doesn't turn out to be
a complete goddamn disaster?

1:14:33.083 --> 1:14:35.708
Jason Orlean?
You want Jason Orlean in that room? Huh?

1:14:35.791 --> 1:14:40.125
I have news for you.
It's already a complete disaster.

1:14:40.208 --> 1:14:43.750
They're talking about letting
a comet the size of a mountain

1:14:43.833 --> 1:14:46.625
hit the planet to jack up
a cell phone company's stock!

1:14:46.708 --> 1:14:49.916
You better take that down
about four or five notches now.

1:14:50.000 --> 1:14:53.625
Were you yelling about that mission?
Why were you talking about cell phones?

1:14:53.708 --> 1:14:56.750
My friend was just theorizing
as to what's going on.

1:14:56.833 --> 1:14:58.291
We're confused too.

1:14:58.375 --> 1:15:01.458
That's an awfully official-looking
White House badge you got there.

1:15:01.541 --> 1:15:03.291
I don't know why I have this on.

1:15:03.375 --> 1:15:05.125
Listen, just tell us what's going on.

1:15:05.208 --> 1:15:07.625
I got three scared kids at home.
Just tell us something.

1:15:07.708 --> 1:15:10.333
I understand.
I wish I could share information, but--

1:15:10.416 --> 1:15:12.958
We're people just like you.
We deserve to know!

1:15:13.041 --> 1:15:13.916
They're right.

1:15:14.958 --> 1:15:16.083
They deserve to know.

1:15:17.000 --> 1:15:18.833
Do you really wanna know what's going on?

1:15:18.916 --> 1:15:20.041
-[woman] Yeah.
-[man] Please.

1:15:20.125 --> 1:15:22.583
-[Oglethorpe] Kate, don't. Kate.
-[Mindy] Kate.

1:15:23.541 --> 1:15:28.958
They found a bunch of gold and diamonds
and rare shit on the comet.

1:15:29.041 --> 1:15:29.875
[sighs]

1:15:29.958 --> 1:15:32.166
So they're gonna let it hit the planet

1:15:32.250 --> 1:15:36.416
to make a bunch of rich people
even more disgustingly rich!

1:15:42.916 --> 1:15:44.000
[woman] Fuck you!

1:15:44.083 --> 1:15:46.083
[people clamoring]

1:15:47.458 --> 1:15:49.250
[people shouting and screaming]

1:15:54.708 --> 1:15:56.500
[officer] No camera!

1:15:56.583 --> 1:15:58.541
…everything I could, they won't listen.

1:15:58.625 --> 1:15:59.958
[Kate] Surprise, surprise.

1:16:00.041 --> 1:16:02.916
Now, I'm starting to think
you just like riling people up.

1:16:03.000 --> 1:16:04.958
I'm so sorry, Kate. Really, I am.

1:16:05.041 --> 1:16:07.041
[Kate] Oh, Randall. God.

1:16:07.875 --> 1:16:09.875
Where's Brie Evantee?

1:16:09.958 --> 1:16:12.375
Shouldn't you two
be playing footsie in a restaurant

1:16:12.458 --> 1:16:14.583
that only serves cubes and foam?

1:16:14.666 --> 1:16:18.083
Well, she ain't wrong.
You did lose the thread in a big way.

1:16:18.166 --> 1:16:21.375
And what do you suggest we do?
An online petition, huh?

1:16:21.458 --> 1:16:24.416
You want to hold…
Get a mob and hold up picket signs?

1:16:24.500 --> 1:16:26.958
You wanna overthrow the government?
I mean, look at this.

1:16:27.041 --> 1:16:28.875
[Kate] I can't! My head is in a bag!

1:16:28.958 --> 1:16:31.583
[agent] Sorry, Dr. Mindy.
White House wants her off the grid.

1:16:31.666 --> 1:16:33.166
-Come on, now. Look--
-[agent] Now.

1:16:33.250 --> 1:16:35.958
[Kate] Wait. What does that mean?
What the hell does that mean?

1:16:36.041 --> 1:16:38.416
-What does "off the grid" mean?
-[Mindy] Hey, Kate.

1:16:39.291 --> 1:16:42.416
Oh, gosh. Kate! Are you okay?

1:16:42.500 --> 1:16:45.458
[people shouting indistinctly]

1:16:45.541 --> 1:16:48.833
Teddy, come on!
What choice do I have here?

1:16:51.166 --> 1:16:53.541
A man's always got choices, Randall!

1:16:53.625 --> 1:16:56.458
Sometimes you just gotta
choose the good one!

1:16:56.541 --> 1:16:57.791
[dog barking]

1:16:57.875 --> 1:17:00.041
[uneasy music playing]

1:17:03.083 --> 1:17:04.708
[man] Miss Katelyn Dibiasky,

1:17:04.791 --> 1:17:08.208
the charges against you are
violation of national security secrets,

1:17:08.291 --> 1:17:11.083
inciting a riot,
and destruction of private property

1:17:11.166 --> 1:17:13.666
owned by Bojo Mambo's Shrimp LLC.

1:17:13.750 --> 1:17:14.583
What? I didn't--

1:17:14.666 --> 1:17:17.583
However, the Attorney General
is willing to not pursue prosecution

1:17:17.666 --> 1:17:19.208
if you will agree to the following:

1:17:19.291 --> 1:17:21.958
