[people chanting]

1:47:36.875 --> 1:47:40.291
[all chanting] Don't look up.

1:47:44.541 --> 1:47:46.291
The hell is that?

1:47:47.583 --> 1:47:49.000
[people continue chanting]

1:47:52.416 --> 1:47:54.583
Fucking lied to us.

1:47:56.125 --> 1:47:59.041
-The president just texted me.
-[glass shattering]

1:47:59.125 --> 1:48:02.583
-"Don't trip. It's all good. Don't trip."
-[people shouting and booing]

1:48:05.000 --> 1:48:06.000
Hey, now.

1:48:06.583 --> 1:48:09.250
You cut my face, you fucking rednecks!

1:48:14.583 --> 1:48:16.875
[wind blowing]

1:48:22.041 --> 1:48:24.375
[Yule] Man, there hasn't been
a car in, like, an hour.

1:48:25.875 --> 1:48:28.541
[Mindy] Yep.
Everyone's watching the BASH launch.

1:48:31.041 --> 1:48:32.333
What are we doing again?

1:48:35.000 --> 1:48:39.416
I told you. We're, uh…
We're gonna go buy some groceries.

1:48:43.041 --> 1:48:44.916
[song playing on radio]

1:48:45.583 --> 1:48:46.833
[volume increases]

1:48:48.041 --> 1:48:53.250
The Mills Brothers. Great band.
You know, Duke Ellington found this band.

1:48:55.958 --> 1:49:00.000
I think they were originally called
the Four Kings of Harmony.

1:49:01.541 --> 1:49:05.666
♪ We'll call on each memory
Till then… ♪

1:49:05.750 --> 1:49:08.208
"Till Then," this is the song.
It's about, uh…

1:49:09.208 --> 1:49:11.458
It's about soldiers
going off to World War II

1:49:11.541 --> 1:49:13.375
and thinking about home.

1:49:16.625 --> 1:49:17.708
Listen to this part.

1:49:17.791 --> 1:49:20.958
♪ Although there are oceans… ♪

1:49:21.041 --> 1:49:27.041
"Although there are oceans we must cross
and mountains that we must climb…"

1:49:28.541 --> 1:49:31.541
♪ I know every gain… ♪

1:49:31.625 --> 1:49:34.708
"I know that every gain must have a loss."

1:49:34.791 --> 1:49:36.625
♪ So pray that our loss… ♪

1:49:36.708 --> 1:49:40.708
"So pray that our loss
is nothing but time."

1:49:40.791 --> 1:49:46.458
♪ Till then, let's dream
Of what there will be ♪

1:49:46.541 --> 1:49:49.083
-[Yule] Okay, I gotta ask you something.
-What?

1:49:51.666 --> 1:49:53.666
Dr. Mindy, can I be vulnerable
in your car?

1:49:53.750 --> 1:49:55.125
[Mindy] Yeah, go ahead.

1:49:57.083 --> 1:49:58.875
I've never met anyone like you

1:49:58.958 --> 1:50:01.166
and I feel a connection to you
on a level that…

1:50:04.333 --> 1:50:06.250
I don't know,
I haven't felt with anyone else,

1:50:06.333 --> 1:50:08.375
and going out on a limb,

1:50:08.458 --> 1:50:10.458
but would you want to spend
more time together?

1:50:10.541 --> 1:50:14.958
-[song stops playing]
-Maybe even get engaged or something?

1:50:15.041 --> 1:50:16.083
[chuckles]

1:50:16.166 --> 1:50:18.000
-Wow.
-[Yule] Are you laughing?

1:50:18.875 --> 1:50:20.125
-No?
-[Kate] I'm smiling.

1:50:21.541 --> 1:50:23.541
-Well, sure.
-[Mindy] This is sweet.

1:50:23.625 --> 1:50:26.875
-Why not?
-This is pretty sweet.

1:50:29.625 --> 1:50:33.333
[rumbling]

1:50:37.291 --> 1:50:41.791
[Orlean hesitates] And you read
the tea leaves for Dr. Mindy.

1:50:41.875 --> 1:50:43.875
-You showed him the algorithm.
-[Peter] Oh, yeah.

1:50:43.958 --> 1:50:46.041
[Orlean] You really shook him
with that information.

1:50:46.125 --> 1:50:48.916
-How he was gonna die.
-[Peter] Yeah, it is shaking.

1:50:49.625 --> 1:50:51.916
It got me so excited
to know about my own death.

1:50:52.000 --> 1:50:53.791
[both laughing]

1:50:54.583 --> 1:50:57.208
I don't think I wanna know.
Yes, I do. I wanna to know.

1:50:57.291 --> 1:51:01.541
You're gonna be eaten by a Bronteroc.
We don't know what it means.

1:51:01.625 --> 1:51:03.583
-A what?
-A Bronteroc.

1:51:05.208 --> 1:51:07.708
-Oh.
-Okay, people, we have clear skies.

1:51:07.791 --> 1:51:09.458
[pensive music playing]

1:51:09.541 --> 1:51:12.750
And we are a go for the BEAD launch.

1:51:12.833 --> 1:51:13.958
Madam President?

1:51:14.041 --> 1:51:18.583
Citizens of planet Earth. Now…

1:51:19.541 --> 1:51:23.250
Look at this, Kate. They have wild salmon.

1:51:23.333 --> 1:51:26.416
Look at the difference between that
and the farm-raised stuff.

1:51:26.500 --> 1:51:29.708
You see how that looks just…
I don't know. Looks fake, right?

1:51:30.833 --> 1:51:33.375
Hey, why don't you go find some, uh…

1:51:33.458 --> 1:51:35.958
What are the little potatoes called,
the tiny ones?

1:51:36.041 --> 1:51:37.166
-Fingerling potatoes?
-Yeah.

1:51:37.250 --> 1:51:39.750
-I fucking love fingerling potatoes.
-Let's get finger…

1:51:39.833 --> 1:51:41.333
Do you wanna say something too?

1:51:41.416 --> 1:51:42.708
That was beautiful. Yeah.

1:51:43.666 --> 1:51:47.791
What up, world? Jason Orlean,
uh, Chief of Staff, United States.

1:51:47.875 --> 1:51:48.833
Um…

1:51:49.875 --> 1:51:53.458
I've been noticing a lot of prayers
recently for people during this time

1:51:54.291 --> 1:51:55.750
and I commend that, um,

1:51:55.833 --> 1:52:02.125
but I also wanna give a prayer for stuff.

1:52:03.625 --> 1:52:08.916
There's dope stuff, like material stuff,
like sick apartments and watches,

1:52:09.000 --> 1:52:11.750
and cars, um, and clothes and shit

1:52:11.833 --> 1:52:16.416
that could all go away
and I don't wanna see that stuff go away.

1:52:16.500 --> 1:52:18.833
So I'm gonna say a prayer
for that stuff. Amen.

1:52:21.958 --> 1:52:25.041
[man on TV] Just a quiet trepidation
among this much smaller crowd.

1:52:25.125 --> 1:52:27.000
I can hear the sounds
of some people praying.

1:52:27.083 --> 1:52:29.166
[Peter] Okay, Anderson, let's go get it.

1:52:29.250 --> 1:52:32.500
Yes, sir. Here we go, people.

1:52:33.291 --> 1:52:34.125
Ten.

1:52:34.208 --> 1:52:41.125
Ten, nine, eight, seven, six,

1:52:41.833 --> 1:52:43.875
five, four…

1:52:46.791 --> 1:52:48.791
[uneasy music playing]

1:52:55.500 --> 1:52:56.625
[doorbell rings]

1:53:02.666 --> 1:53:03.500
Hey.

1:53:04.958 --> 1:53:05.791
Hi.

1:53:05.875 --> 1:53:07.708
[flames roaring]

1:53:09.166 --> 1:53:11.541
[dramatic music playing]

1:53:16.583 --> 1:53:19.541
We, uh, got some groceries.

1:53:20.958 --> 1:53:23.541
[dramatic music playing]

1:53:28.916 --> 1:53:30.291
Yo, what was that?

1:53:30.375 --> 1:53:32.291
-We lost BEAD number 12.
-[alarm blaring]

1:53:35.208 --> 1:53:36.833
[man] BEAD number 22 failed to launch.

1:53:37.708 --> 1:53:40.541
It's fine. It's fine.

1:53:40.625 --> 1:53:44.666
We had anticipated a margin for error.

1:53:44.750 --> 1:53:46.250
Everything is fine.

1:53:46.333 --> 1:53:50.833
I was hoping
we could, um, have a family dinner.

1:53:50.916 --> 1:53:52.291
[Evan and Marshall] Hey, Dad.

1:53:52.375 --> 1:53:54.458
-Hey, guys. Hey.
-Hey.

1:54:00.833 --> 1:54:01.750
What do you say?

1:54:04.166 --> 1:54:05.000
Yeah.

1:54:05.916 --> 1:54:07.291
-[Mindy] Thank you.
-Yeah.

1:54:07.791 --> 1:54:10.000
-This is, uh… This is Kate.
-Oh, hi.

1:54:10.083 --> 1:54:11.916
-Hello. Hi, Kate.
-Let me grab those bags.

1:54:12.000 --> 1:54:13.750
-Nice to meet you. I'm Yule.
-Yule.

1:54:13.833 --> 1:54:16.000
I'm FirePuma142 on Twitch. You game?

1:54:16.625 --> 1:54:18.125
It's really doubtful she knows.

1:54:18.208 --> 1:54:19.833
-You're right.
-Who said I game?

1:54:21.000 --> 1:54:23.333
I… I got these for you.

1:54:25.208 --> 1:54:27.166
Thank you. That's really sweet, honey.

1:54:33.375 --> 1:54:35.375
I'm so sorry. You have no idea.

1:54:37.208 --> 1:54:39.916
-I really am.
-[sighs] I know. I know.

1:54:40.750 --> 1:54:43.875
-I've missed you.
-I missed you so much.

1:54:50.875 --> 1:54:53.625
When we dated in college,
I fucked Aaron Tran.

1:54:55.875 --> 1:54:56.708
Oh?

1:54:57.333 --> 1:54:58.708
Yeah, so, uh…

1:55:02.458 --> 1:55:04.041
[Motown song playing on speakers]

1:55:04.125 --> 1:55:05.625
[indistinct chatter]

1:55:14.541 --> 1:55:16.833
-That is really good.
-Really good, right?

1:55:27.708 --> 1:55:30.000
-Hey, everybody.
-Hey!

1:55:30.083 --> 1:55:32.791
-Sorry I'm late, but not empty-handed.
-Hey, my friend.

1:55:33.875 --> 1:55:37.375
Evan, Marshall, June,
this is Dr. Oglethorpe.

1:55:37.458 --> 1:55:39.125
[indistinct chatter]

1:55:39.208 --> 1:55:41.208
[dramatic music playing]

1:55:52.000 --> 1:55:54.875
BEADs have approached
optimal escape velocity

1:55:54.958 --> 1:55:59.625
and now approaching Comet Dibiasky
and are ready for attachment mode.

1:56:12.750 --> 1:56:14.041
-[crash on video]
-[gasps]

1:56:15.000 --> 1:56:17.625
-[alarm blaring]
-Uh… Okay. All right.

1:56:17.708 --> 1:56:20.833
Eight and 27 are lost
due to lateral control malfunction.

1:56:21.750 --> 1:56:24.666
Okay, so, now… Now, Peter…

1:56:24.750 --> 1:56:28.958
Peter, we're six drones down.
Is this thing still gonna work?

1:56:29.041 --> 1:56:34.875
Well, the engineer's assured me
that yes, 24 drones is enough.

1:56:35.958 --> 1:56:38.958
Well, how many can we lose?

1:56:41.583 --> 1:56:43.083
[hesitates] How many more?

1:56:43.166 --> 1:56:44.791
[alarm blaring]

1:56:46.625 --> 1:56:50.250
We're being told that several
of the BEADS have exploded on launch.

1:56:51.291 --> 1:56:54.125
-Got the head seat right there.
-[Oglethorpe chuckles]

1:56:54.208 --> 1:56:56.791
You're way too kind, Randall. Thank you.

1:56:56.875 --> 1:56:57.875
[Mindy] Big Doctor.

1:56:57.958 --> 1:56:59.166
Do you want more wine?

1:57:00.291 --> 1:57:02.291
-Hey, cheers, everyone. Huh?
-[Oglethorpe] Cheers.

1:57:02.375 --> 1:57:03.416
-Cheers.
-[Mindy] Love you.

1:57:03.500 --> 1:57:05.250
-Love you.
-Thank you so much for having us.

1:57:05.333 --> 1:57:06.583
Thank you for being here.

1:57:06.666 --> 1:57:08.208
-It's so special.
-Thank you.

1:57:08.291 --> 1:57:10.291
[dramatic music playing]

1:57:20.958 --> 1:57:24.166
Commence simultaneous
explosive separation stage now.

1:57:26.125 --> 1:57:27.458
-[gasps]
-[alarm blaring]

1:57:27.541 --> 1:57:29.708
[Jason] Yo. Yo. Mom.

1:57:29.791 --> 1:57:33.000
[dramatic music playing]

1:57:39.708 --> 1:57:40.750
[Oglethorpe] Beautiful.

1:57:41.333 --> 1:57:43.250
-[Mindy] Thank you, pal.
-Yeah.

1:57:43.333 --> 1:57:48.083
Yeah, it really is.
And it's really good to have you home.

1:57:49.750 --> 1:57:51.500
[Kate] Dr. Mindy got really famous.

1:57:51.583 --> 1:57:54.125
Oh. Oh, yeah, I forgot about that.

1:57:54.208 --> 1:57:55.791
-That's right. Okay.
-[laughter]

1:57:56.708 --> 1:58:00.625
Yep, I was on, uh, magazine covers
and everything. I know.

1:58:01.291 --> 1:58:03.375
-[Kate] You looked great.
-I'll take your shots.

1:58:03.458 --> 1:58:04.541
[laughter]

1:58:06.916 --> 1:58:07.750
[kisses]

1:58:07.833 --> 1:58:09.458
-[Mrs. Mindy] I love you.
-Love you too.

1:58:10.875 --> 1:58:13.500
-[intense music playing]
-All right. We need a report.

1:58:13.583 --> 1:58:16.166
Need a full status report
on the explosive devices.

1:58:16.250 --> 1:58:19.416
Get on it.
Still waiting for a full status report.

1:58:19.500 --> 1:58:21.333
-[cell phone ringing]
-[gasps]

1:58:21.416 --> 1:58:22.458
[Anderson] All right.

1:58:22.541 --> 1:58:27.625
[breathing heavily] President Qi of China
says that the comet is still whole.

1:58:27.708 --> 1:58:29.791
We got four misfires and sync was off.

1:58:30.625 --> 1:58:31.625
It's still intact.

1:58:31.708 --> 1:58:32.875
[Peter] What was that?

1:58:33.541 --> 1:58:35.958
We've got four misfires
and the sync was off.

1:58:36.791 --> 1:58:40.958
Okay. We're all fine. Everyone's fine.

1:58:41.708 --> 1:58:44.791
It's gonna be all right.
If you'll excuse me. [chuckles]

1:58:44.875 --> 1:58:46.125
Nature calls.

1:58:46.208 --> 1:58:49.208
I'm just gonna go to the restroom
for a moment.

1:58:52.666 --> 1:58:55.541
Yes, uh, I think
that I should also step out

1:58:55.625 --> 1:58:57.333
to the restroom for a moment.

1:58:58.541 --> 1:59:01.041
-[alarm continues blaring]
-[indistinct chatter]

1:59:03.583 --> 1:59:05.583
-[Jason] Should I…
-No, I'll be fine.

1:59:06.625 --> 1:59:08.125
Sir, the president.

1:59:08.875 --> 1:59:11.000
We need to know
what the mission status is.

1:59:13.166 --> 1:59:14.750
She's coming right back.

1:59:15.416 --> 1:59:18.041
Screw this. I'm going to see my husband.

1:59:19.541 --> 1:59:21.250
[people clamoring]

1:59:21.333 --> 1:59:24.625
I'm sorry. I've got a 20-year-old
daughter. I've got to go see her.

1:59:25.291 --> 1:59:26.625
[man] I'm doin' an 8-ball.

1:59:27.791 --> 1:59:28.833
[woman] Oh, shit!

1:59:28.916 --> 1:59:30.625
She's coming. She's coming back.

1:59:30.708 --> 1:59:32.208
[people clamoring in panic]

1:59:37.041 --> 1:59:39.250
[Orlean] Hello, there's a ship.

1:59:39.791 --> 1:59:43.916
In case we were wrong,
and clearly, we were wrong.

1:59:44.000 --> 1:59:46.458
Of course you've got a ship.

1:59:46.541 --> 1:59:48.125
[Orlean] It holds 2,000.

1:59:48.208 --> 1:59:51.458
It's state-of-the-art cryo-chambers,
and it's set to find

1:59:51.541 --> 1:59:54.666
the nearest Earth-like planet
in a Goldilocks Zone so…

1:59:54.750 --> 1:59:55.625
Hmm.

1:59:55.708 --> 1:59:57.125
There's room for you and one other.

1:59:58.166 --> 2:00:00.250
Brie, your wife, your call.

2:00:02.708 --> 2:00:09.500
I'm good, but thank you for the offer.
You, uh… You have fun with Jason.

2:00:11.541 --> 2:00:12.500
Jason?

2:00:15.250 --> 2:00:16.375
Oh, shit.

2:00:17.000 --> 2:00:18.583
[alarm blaring]

2:00:20.083 --> 2:00:21.083
She's coming back.

2:00:22.125 --> 2:00:24.125
[uneasy music playing]

2:00:30.125 --> 2:00:33.041
I'm thankful for that night
I fell asleep out in the backyard.

2:00:33.791 --> 2:00:36.166
-Woke up face-to-face with a baby deer.
-I remember that.

2:00:36.250 --> 2:00:38.708
-Yeah.
-Yep. It was the best day of my life.

2:00:40.791 --> 2:00:41.708
[kisses]

2:00:50.166 --> 2:00:51.375
I'm grateful…

2:00:58.750 --> 2:01:00.666
[shakily] I'm grateful we tried.

2:01:03.541 --> 2:01:06.000
Man, oh, man, did we try.

2:01:08.458 --> 2:01:13.791
Well, we're not the most religious here
in the Mindy household,

2:01:13.875 --> 2:01:17.500
but, um, maybe we should say "amen"?
Should we do that?

2:01:17.583 --> 2:01:19.041
[Mrs. Mindy] Don't look at me.

2:01:19.875 --> 2:01:23.833
[chuckling] I don't know how to…
What, you just say, "Amen"? I don't…

2:01:24.541 --> 2:01:25.750
-I got this.
-Wrap it up?

2:01:26.416 --> 2:01:27.250
I got it.

2:01:38.750 --> 2:01:41.000
Dearest Father and Almighty Creator…

2:01:42.666 --> 2:01:43.708
[sighs]

2:01:44.875 --> 2:01:48.708
…we ask for Your grace tonight,
despite our pride.

2:01:50.416 --> 2:01:54.291
Your forgiveness, despite our doubt.

2:01:57.625 --> 2:01:59.125
Most of all, Lord…

2:02:01.125 --> 2:02:05.791
we ask for Your love
to soothe us through these dark times.

2:02:08.291 --> 2:02:10.500
May we face whatever is to come…

2:02:10.583 --> 2:02:12.708
[music continues playing]

2:02:12.791 --> 2:02:18.583
…in Your divine will with courage
and open hearts of acceptance.

2:02:21.833 --> 2:02:24.291
-Amen.
-[Oglethorpe] Amen.

2:02:25.541 --> 2:02:27.708
Wow. Youse got some church game.

2:02:29.625 --> 2:02:30.750
That was beautiful.

2:02:34.166 --> 2:02:36.125
The comet remains intact.

2:02:36.208 --> 2:02:39.166
[people clamoring in panic]

2:02:42.875 --> 2:02:44.541
We just never… [sighs]

2:02:46.750 --> 2:02:50.208
Of course, there's only one story
everyone's talking about tonight.

2:02:50.791 --> 2:02:52.791
Topless urgent care centers.

2:02:53.458 --> 2:02:56.833
[people clamoring]

2:02:58.833 --> 2:02:59.916
[gunfire]

2:03:03.000 --> 2:03:04.458
[sighs] Sit.

2:03:06.458 --> 2:03:10.791
Or… we can fuck…

2:03:10.875 --> 2:03:12.750
[breathing heavily]

2:03:12.833 --> 2:03:14.666
…or pray, or…

2:03:18.791 --> 2:03:22.291
Honestly, I think
I'd just rather drink and…

2:03:24.250 --> 2:03:25.916
talk shit about people.

2:03:27.208 --> 2:03:29.708
[rapid gunfire]

2:03:32.208 --> 2:03:33.833
You'll never take me alive!

2:03:37.041 --> 2:03:37.958
Look out!

2:03:38.541 --> 2:03:39.750
[dog barking]

2:03:47.500 --> 2:03:49.041
[indistinct chatter on TV]

2:03:53.208 --> 2:03:54.875
-[grunting]
-[woman screaming]

2:04:02.083 --> 2:04:03.916
[people screaming]

2:04:09.666 --> 2:04:10.791
[birds chirping]

2:04:25.833 --> 2:04:27.416
[shouting]

2:04:28.958 --> 2:04:30.000
[indistinct chatter]

2:04:30.083 --> 2:04:32.916
I'm definitely gonna have
some more of this apple pie. It's so good.

2:04:33.000 --> 2:04:35.791
It's actually store-bought,
but you really can't tell.

2:04:37.666 --> 2:04:42.208
If I'm to be completely honest,
which at this moment, why not?

2:04:43.208 --> 2:04:46.916
I actually like the junky taste
of store-bought better than homemade.

2:04:47.666 --> 2:04:48.666
You gotta be kidding me.

2:04:48.750 --> 2:04:52.166
No, I'm not kidding.

2:04:53.458 --> 2:04:56.666
You know what? I know what he means.
It's like a childhood memory thing.

2:04:59.708 --> 2:05:02.541
[piano music playing]

2:05:02.625 --> 2:05:04.541
[people clamoring]

2:05:06.625 --> 2:05:08.458
[explosions]

2:05:16.208 --> 2:05:19.208
[music continues playing]

2:05:30.125 --> 2:05:31.583
[electricity crackling]

2:05:31.666 --> 2:05:33.583
Nothing is better than homemade, right?

2:05:33.666 --> 2:05:37.208
This coffee doesn't taste
store-bought. Is it?

2:05:37.291 --> 2:05:39.666
I grind my own beans. Yeah.

2:05:39.750 --> 2:05:41.375
Yeah, Dad's kind of a coffee nut.

2:05:41.458 --> 2:05:43.708
Every time you have coffee,
you have to grind your beans?

2:05:44.708 --> 2:05:48.666
Randall is very particular
